Of course. Here is a standard `.gitignore` file for your Node.js project.

Create this file in the **root directory** of your project (`weather-playlist-api/.gitignore`). Its purpose is to tell Git which files and folders it should not track or upload to a repository like GitHub.

-----

### .gitignore

```
# Dependencies
# This folder contains all the downloaded libraries. It can be huge and
# should be regenerated by running `npm install`.
node_modules/

# Environment Variables
# This file contains your secret API keys and should NEVER be shared.
.env

# Logs
# Log files are specific to your local machine.
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
*.log

# Operating System Generated Files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor Directories
# These contain user-specific settings for code editors.
.idea/
.vscode/
```